title: Bump ansi_term from 0.12.0 to 0.12.1

labels.name: dependencies
labels.description: Pull requests that update a dependency file

body:
Bumps [ansi_term](https://github.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term) from 0.12.0 to 0.12.1.
Commits - [`ff7eba9`](https://github.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/commit/ff7eba98d55ad609c7fcc8c7bb0859b37c7545cc) v0.12.1 - [`e2801d3`](https://github.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/commit/e2801d373cf64a48c01e9dfb211feb8350b2b3cd) Merge pull request [#53](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/issues/53) from manuthambi/master - [`bad66a3`](https://github.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/commit/bad66a3a9033ff112e5e518b0e2fbd79c0d3652d) Merge pull request [#52](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/issues/52) from rivy/fix.win-build - [`50e1a14`](https://github.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/commit/50e1a14d95c887df2d896df5ac2cfa2c0f4f8282) docs ~ convert to img.shields.io build badges (adding AppVeyor CI build badge) - [`9a972ed`](https://github.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/commit/9a972ed52a85f34130d071c982fa129297585fd0) change ~ increase windows early version compatibility - [`f30e601`](https://github.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/commit/f30e6011537d8bb3fe3a6dff8dbf9710cff0979d) refactor ~ load winapi constants into the `enable_ansi_support()` namespace - [`85883f4`](https://github.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/commit/85883f412c83f5400247073d0d293fbd841cb568) fix minimum rust version - [`dc0e818`](https://github.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/commit/dc0e8182ec3479816a637dedf428fd38636dfaca) fix 'long_and_detailed' test for differing `rustc` versions - [`0cbe910`](https://github.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/commit/0cbe910015b3762f03adf77bee17514157f332d6) Updated the documentation for Style::infix() and Colour::infix() to make clear - [`6e57df3`](https://github.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/commit/6e57df3afe4d2360dac5ac25d52a2339c938e9d3) Bugfix: In the Display implementation of Infix, after a reset, use the correc... - Additional commits viewable in [compare view](https://github.com/ogham/rust-ansi-term/compare/v0.12.0...v0.12.1)
